---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const locale = 'en' as const;
const STONKS_SITE = 'https://stonksbots.com/';
const STONKS_TRADER = 'https://t.me/stonks_sniper_bot';
const TG_STONKSONTON = 'https://t.me/stonksonton';
const STONKS_PUMP_LAUNCH = 'https://stonkslabs.com/launch/ton';
const STONKS_PUMP_DOCS = 'https://stonks-bot.gitbook.io/stonks-bot-manual/stonks.pump-launchpad';
const YT_VIDEO_ID = 'IaodzcNhy_4';
const YT_EMBED = `https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/${YT_VIDEO_ID}?start=2&rel=0`;
---

<Layout
  locale={locale}
  pathWithoutLocale="/stonks"
  title="sTONks — the on-chain ecosystem behind $CULO"
  description="What sTONks is, how the stonks.pump launchpad works, and how $CULO was launched on it."
>
  <article class="news-article stonks-article">
    <div class="breadcrumb">
      <a href="/">News</a> &nbsp;/&nbsp; <span>sTONks</span>
    </div>

    <header class="stonks-hero">
      <img class="stonks-logo" src="/stonks.jpg" alt="sTONks logo" width="120" height="120" />
      <div>
        <span class="stonks-kicker">TON · Build · Tokenize · Trade</span>
        <h1>sTONks — the on-chain ecosystem behind $CULO</h1>
      </div>
    </header>

    <p class="article-summary">
      $CULO was not deployed in a vacuum. It was launched on
      <strong><a href={STONKS_SITE} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">sTONks</a></strong>,
      an end-to-end on-chain platform that lets you build, deploy, tokenize and trade — all in
      one place, all on TON. Here is what that means.
    </p>

    <div class="body">
      <h2>What sTONks actually is</h2>
      <p>
        sTONks is not just a launchpad. It is a four-stage on-chain pipeline that closes the loop
        between writing code and trading the result:
      </p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Build</strong> — agentic LLM pipelines (Claude, GPT, Gemini, Grok or any model) write the code. Humans review, edit, ship.</li>
        <li><strong>Deploy</strong> — one-click deploy to managed infra, your own VPS, bare metal, Telegram Cloud or LLM APIs. Encrypted secrets vault, instant logs, autoscaling. Zero ops.</li>
        <li><strong>Tokenize</strong> — fairlaunch, presale, bonding curve, revshare, dividends or a fully custom tokenomic. Or skip tokens entirely and accept crypto payments.</li>
        <li><strong>Govern</strong> — Roundtable DAO with an Oracle AI that audits every commit, deploy and milestone against the roadmap holders voted on. Closed-source projects too.</li>
      </ol>
      <p>
        The platform's own numbers (as published on stonksbots.com): <strong>2,170 projects launched</strong>,
        <strong>12,000+ monthly active traders</strong>, <strong>41,300 TON in ecosystem liquidity</strong>,
        and <strong>160,000 TON in dividends</strong> already paid out to holders.
      </p>

      <h2>The trading side</h2>
      <p>
        On top of the build pipeline, sTONks ships a full trading stack:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Trading Terminal</strong> — multi-wallet, sniper bot, TradingView charts, limit orders, on-chain fills, sub-100ms execution.</li>
        <li><strong>Telegram trading bot</strong> — <a href={STONKS_TRADER} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">@stonks_sniper_bot</a>: full terminal in a DM. Buy, sell, snipe, track wallets, instant PnL.</li>
        <li><strong>Stonks Gem Bot</strong> + <strong>New Pairs Bot</strong> — alpha straight to Telegram, no gatekeeping, every launch is fair.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Real RWA — token cryptographically tied to a repo</h2>
      <p>
        This is the part that makes sTONks different. Every token launched on the platform is
        bound on-chain to its project's GitHub repository. Holders watch real commits land in
        real time. Even closed-source projects can prove progress: the AI Oracle audits each
        commit, deploy and milestone against the on-chain roadmap before the token keeps its
        verified status.
      </p>
      <p>
        Supply, fees and curves are locked on-chain at launch — no hidden mints, no dev
        unlocks, no rug levers. The binding between token and code is publicly verifiable.
      </p>

      <h2>How $CULO was born</h2>
      <p>
        $CULO was launched on sTONks using the <strong>Deploy-with-TAX</strong> tokenomic — not
        the bonding-curve route. That means a fixed-supply token with a small fee on every
        buy/sell, instead of a curve-graduated launch. The platform handled the deployment, the
        on-chain tax wiring, and the listing on the integrated trading layer from day one.
      </p>
      <p>
        CuloTon — the news desk you're reading right now — was built around the token. First
        came $CULO; then the editorial layer (this site, the multilingual news pipeline, the
        Telegram bot, the X feed) was added on top so $CULO had something to grow into beyond a
        launch chart.
      </p>

      <h2 id="stonks-pump">stonks.pump — how the launchpad actually works</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>stonks.pump</strong> is the free jetton launchpad inside sTONks — the actual
        surface where a new TON token (like $CULO) gets deployed. The four-stage ecosystem above
        is the platform; stonks.pump is the &quot;launch&quot; button on it. Source:
        <a href={STONKS_PUMP_DOCS} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">stonks-bot manual</a>.
      </p>

      <h3>Launch flow (creator side)</h3>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Open the launcher</strong> — either <a href={STONKS_TRADER} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">@stonks_sniper_bot</a> on Telegram (<code>/start</code> → &quot;🚀 Launch coin&quot;) or the web terminal at <a href={STONKS_PUMP_LAUNCH} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">stonkslabs.com/launch/ton</a>.</li>
        <li><strong>Coin details</strong> — name, symbol, image, description.</li>
        <li><strong>Liquidity mode</strong> — choose <em>Seed LP</em> (you set the LP amount manually) or <em>Virtual LP</em> (algorithmic, equivalent to ~500 TON of liquidity for a flat 3.2 TON fee).</li>
        <li><strong>Tokenomics</strong> — pick <em>Simple coin</em> (no taxes) or <em>Customize</em> for buy/sell taxes (max 30% each), anti-sniper limits, a dev bag (max 5% of supply), marketing wallet and holder reward distribution.</li>
        <li><strong>Deploy</strong> — submit one transaction. Processing time: ~5 min for Seed LP, 1-2 min for Virtual LP.</li>
      </ol>

      <h3>Two liquidity modes side by side</h3>
      <div class="pump-modes">
        <div class="pump-mode">
          <h4>Seed LP</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>You provide the LP yourself, drawn from the deployer wallet.</li>
            <li>Cost: <strong>LP amount + 4 TON</strong>; plus <strong>5% of tax revenue</strong> to the launchpad. Zero-tax launches are free.</li>
            <li>Lets you split tax between marketing wallet and holder rewards.</li>
            <li>Processing ~5 minutes.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="pump-mode">
          <h4>Virtual LP</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>Algorithmic bonding curve — equivalent to <strong>~500 TON</strong> of liquidity for a flat <strong>3.2 TON</strong>.</li>
            <li>Fee: <strong>0.3% (with tax)</strong> or <strong>0.4% (no tax)</strong>; plus 5% of tax revenue.</li>
            <li>All rewards go to holders (no marketing-wallet split in this mode).</li>
            <li>Curve graduates as the real price catches up to the virtual price; processing ~1-2 minutes.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="hint">
        Recommended buffer on the deployer wallet: 5-7 TON for network fees. Total supply is
        fixed at <strong>100 million tokens</strong> regardless of mode.
      </p>

      <h3>Built-in protections</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>LP burned</strong> at launch — the deployer cannot remove liquidity. No rug lever.</li>
        <li><strong>Auto ownership revoke</strong> — mint/burn rights are dropped on the deployer post-launch.</li>
        <li><strong>Anti-sniper</strong> — optional max-buy cap for the first 30 minutes (effectively first 15 per FAQ); excess goes to LP.</li>
        <li><strong>Single-transaction LP add</strong> on STON.fi prevents micro-LP snipes.</li>
        <li><strong>Holder rewards</strong> — when taxes are enabled, distributions to holders begin roughly an hour after launch and depend on volume.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Watch the walkthrough</h3>
      <div class="video-wrap">
        <iframe
          src={YT_EMBED}
          title="stonks.pump launchpad walkthrough"
          loading="lazy"
          allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share"
          allowfullscreen
          referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin"
        ></iframe>
      </div>
      <p class="hint">
        For full official documentation, see the
        <a href={STONKS_PUMP_DOCS} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">stonks.pump manual</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Why it matters for the TON ecosystem</h2>
      <p>
        sTONks lowers the barrier to entry for serious on-chain projects, not just memecoins.
        Anyone with a Telegram account and a TON wallet can ship a real product, tokenize it
        with locked-on-chain tokenomics, and reach an audience that is already trading. That
        fits the TON ethos — the chain is wired directly into Telegram, the largest messaging
        platform people already use every day.
      </p>
      <p>
        For traders, the value prop is simpler: every token on sTONks comes with a verifiable
        link to actual code. Less LARP. More signal.
      </p>

      <h2>Where to go next</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>🌐 <a href={STONKS_SITE} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">stonksbots.com</a> — the official sTONks platform.</li>
        <li>🚀 <a href={STONKS_PUMP_LAUNCH} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">stonkslabs.com/launch/ton</a> — the stonks.pump launcher.</li>
        <li>🤖 <a href={STONKS_TRADER} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">@stonks_sniper_bot</a> — the trading terminal in a Telegram DM.</li>
        <li>💬 <a href={TG_STONKSONTON} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">t.me/stonksonton</a> — the community chat where launches are discussed in real time.</li>
        <li>🟡 <a href="/culo">Track $CULO live</a> — price, FDV, 24h flow, where to buy.</li>
        <li>📰 <a href="/">Latest TON news</a> — full feed, updated every 2 hours.</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        <em>This page is a living explainer based on public information from
        <a href={STONKS_SITE} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">stonksbots.com</a> and the
        <a href={STONKS_PUMP_DOCS} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">stonks.pump manual</a>.
        Spot a fact that needs sharpening? Drop us a tip in the
        <a href="https://t.me/culoton" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">CuloTon Telegram</a>.</em>
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .stonks-hero {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 22px;
    margin: 18px 0 14px;
  }
  .stonks-logo {
    width: 110px;
    height: 110px;
    object-fit: cover;
    border: 2px solid var(--rule);
    border-radius: 0;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .stonks-kicker {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    border: 1px solid var(--accent);
    padding: 3px 8px;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .stonks-article h1 { margin: 0; }
  .pump-modes {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 16px;
    margin: 14px 0 18px;
  }
  .pump-mode {
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    padding: 16px 18px 14px;
    background: var(--bg-section, transparent);
  }
  .pump-mode h4 {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 13px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--accent-hot, var(--accent));
    margin: 0 0 8px;
  }
  .pump-mode ul {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 18px;
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--text-dim);
  }
  .pump-mode li { margin: 4px 0; }
  .pump-mode strong { color: var(--text); }
  .video-wrap {
    position: relative;
    width: 100%;
    aspect-ratio: 16 / 9;
    margin: 16px 0 8px;
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    background: #000;
  }
  .video-wrap iframe {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    border: 0;
  }
  .hint {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--text-mute);
    margin: 6px 0 12px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .stonks-hero { gap: 14px; }
    .stonks-logo { width: 72px; height: 72px; }
    .pump-modes { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
